news.title: US treasury secretary says President's proposed housing tax credits could boost supply
news.para: Yellen said in an interview on MSNBC that Biden's top economic priority was helping Americans deal with higher prices and major living expenses, including the high cost of housing.

news.title: Housing minister says China will improve home sales in 'forceful' way
news.para: China's Minister of Housing and Urban-Rural Development, Ni Hong, pledges to improve home sales in a forceful and orderly way amidst weak demand.

news.title: ED attaches assets worth Rs 367 crore in Bhushan Steel 'bank fraud' case
news.para: A provisional order has been issued under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) to attach the assets that were held "in the name of benamidars/shell entities through dummy directors so as to conceal them and to ensure that they are out of the reach of law enforcement agencies", the ED has said in a statement.

news.title: Six town schemes in Pune may hit poll hurdle unless okayed soon: PMRDA official
news.para: The projects are being planned on the lines of Gujarat model of town planning scheme under which landowners can get back 50% of developed land in the same area.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC inspects construction sites in Juhu for pollution
news.para: Residents of Gulmohar Road in Juhu and JVPD scheme had met the K-West ward officer on Wednesday to complain about the quality of air and that construction projects in the area were not adhering to air pollution mitigation norms.

news.title: Citizens rally against Bengaluru civic body's property tax proposal
news.para: In response, the BBMP Commissioner provided key insights, including the mapping of 22,000 roads under the BBMP jurisdiction. He clarified that property tax will be determined based on the property ID assigned by the BBMP, ensuring differentiation between diverse properties, such as slums in the CBD and upscale villas in Jakkur.

news.title: Poor response to gunthewari scheme; PMC to slash rates
news.para: “The state government has issued a directive, which will enable us to revise regularisation rates. The new rates will be declared soon,” said Prashant Waghmare, the city engineer of the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC).

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM opens two affordable housing complexes in Madurai
news.para: The three-storeyed (G+3) apartment complex in Manjalmedu, constructed under the housing for all scheme, cost a total of 37.3 crore.

news.title: Delhi fire services finds 100 apartments in Dwarka without valid NOC
news.para: The drive follows the tragic incident in Feb in which an 83-year-old woman died and her granddaughter was injured after jumping off their fourth-floor apartment to escape a fire.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government plans new city near Agra
news.para: UP govt plans New Agra Urban Centre near Agra. Consultants sought for Master Plan 2031 to create urban space, transport links, and assess environmental impact.

news.title: Odisha RERA orders promoters to submit declaration mentioning past projects
news.para: ORERA said that while applying for registration of any real estate project, promoters will have to mandatorily submit the self-declaration wherethey will mention all the details of their housing and other projects.

news.title: Bond trustee becomes new petitioner to liquidate China's Kaisa Group
news.para: The latest development came after Broad Peak Investment, which filed the winding-up petition in July in relation to non-payment of onshore bonds worth 170 million yuan ($24 million), sought to withdraw from the case as it has sold the debt holdings earlier this year.

news.title: China Evergrande liquidators appoint legal advisers: Sources
news.para: Global firm Clifford Chance and Hong Kong firms Tanner De Witt and Karas So were mandated recently to provide legal advice on the liquidation, which has been under way for about six weeks, the people added.

news.title: Ghaziabad master plan hits a hurdle fourth time, over green zone now
news.para: The Master Plan 2021, which was to stay in effect until the end of the 2021 financial year, is likely to remain in effect until the new plan is approved by state officials.

news.title: Maharashtra direct KDMC to impose property tax from 27 villages residents as per before 2017 rates
news.para: In a meeting held at Mumbai, the Chief Minister directed Kalyan-Dombivli Municipal Corporation to impose property tax at old rates for residents of 27 villages within its limits.

news.title: Noida: 1,500 stamp duty evasion cases, camp on March 16 to resolve issues
news.para: In Noida and Greater Noida, the properties are registered in different categories like residential, commercial, industrial, institutional, agricultural, etc. Hence, a person cannot use the residential area for commercial activity or any other use.
